# Security headers for Cloudflare Pages. The key privacy line is `connect-src`:
# the browser may only talk to our OWN origin ('self') — which includes the
# same-origin Worker API bound at `/api/*` — and to Cloudflare Web Analytics.
# Nothing else, and never plaintext or the password.
#
# If you instead host the Worker API on `*.workers.dev` (cross-origin from
# Pages), add that exact origin to `connect-src` here.
#
# 'wasm-unsafe-eval' is required to compile the Argon2id hash-wasm module in the
# browser. 'unsafe-inline' for script/style is required by Next.js's static
# runtime. Neither weakens the user-data guarantee — that is enforced by
# `connect-src` allowing only 'self' plus the anonymous-analytics origin.
/*
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' 'wasm-unsafe-eval' https://static.cloudflareinsights.com; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' data:; font-src 'self' data:; connect-src 'self' https://cloudflareinsights.com; object-src 'none'; base-uri 'self'; frame-ancestors 'none'
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=63072000; includeSubDomains; preload
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: no-referrer
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Permissions-Policy: geolocation=(), microphone=(), camera=()
